          "treatment": "IMMEDIATE IV antibiotics: ceftriaxone 2g IV (or cefotaxime). Do not wait for LP or imaging. Steroids: dexamethasone 0.15mg/kg IV if bacterial meningitis suspected (controversial in meningococcal). IV fluids (sepsis protocol). Vasopressors if shock. ICU admission. Notify public health. Chemoprophylaxis for close contacts (ciprofloxacin or rifampicin)."
        },
        {
          "severity": "meningococcal sepsis / Waterhouse-Friderichsen",
          "criteria": "purpura fulminans, shock, DIC, adrenal haemorrhage",
          "treatment": "Aggressive fluid resuscitation. Vasopressors (norepinephrine). Stress-dose hydrocortisone (if adrenal failure suspected). Correct coagulopathy (FFP, platelets, cryoprecipitate). Consider activated protein C (controversial). Surgical debridement of necrotic tissue. ECMO if refractory shock."
        }
